The US military on Wednesday said it had conducted an airstrike against Taliban forces, just days after signing a historic peace deal with the militant group. In a tweet, US military spokesman Colonel Sonny Legget said it was a "defensive strike" to counter an assault on Afghan government forces. This was the first US strike on Taliban forces in 11 days. The two parties had agreed to reduce violence in the lead up to signing the peace deal this past weekend. On Tuesday, several attacks were carried out against Afghan forces, resulting in the death of at least 14 security force members. more to come.. kp/rtÂ (AP, dpa, Reuters) Every evening, DW sends out a selection of the day's news and features. Sign up here